You just want to do him.
l know you.

538
00:33:04,109 --> 00:33:05,133
You know you.

539
00:33:05,210 --> 00:33:07,701
He is cute.

540
00:33:07,779 --> 00:33:09,440
Mm, sort of.
He's not my type.

541
00:33:09,514 --> 00:33:12,312
Smart, sensitive,
wants only to talk about you--

542
00:33:12,384 --> 00:33:13,908
how is that not your type?

543
00:33:14,019 --> 00:33:17,045
Sam, l can't read,
l can't sleep...

544
00:33:17,122 --> 00:33:19,920
And l'm sure Dr. Dave will be
able to give you what you need.

545
00:33:20,025 --> 00:33:21,822
l'm serious.

546
00:33:21,893 --> 00:33:23,918
Okay, okay,
did he sit behind his desk

547
00:33:24,062 --> 00:33:26,155
or did he pull his chair
close to you?

548
00:33:26,231 --> 00:33:28,665
Close to me.

549
00:33:28,733 --> 00:33:33,500
Did he... lean over like this?

550
00:33:35,240 --> 00:33:36,969
Did he look into your eyes
like this?

551
00:33:38,844 --> 00:33:40,175
You're going to do him.

552
00:33:40,245 --> 00:33:41,177
Sam...

553
00:33:41,246 --> 00:33:44,943
Come on, how long has it been,
sophomore year?

554
00:33:45,016 --> 00:33:48,952
What if it's rusty... or broken?

555
00:33:49,020 --> 00:33:50,851
l still feel like
l'm betraying him.

556
00:33:50,922 --> 00:33:53,755
Embry? Please.

557
00:33:53,825 --> 00:33:56,623
What if Embry comes back?

558
00:33:56,695 --> 00:34:01,359
He'd... wreck your life
just like before.

559
00:34:03,401 --> 00:34:06,571
Listen, l want
to tell you something.

560
00:34:06,638 --> 00:34:09,732
Um, l believe your friend,
Embry, is dead.

561
00:34:12,510 --> 00:34:14,910
He had two airline tickets
for Athens, Greece.

562
00:34:15,046 --> 00:34:16,911
Never used.
No credit activity.

563
00:34:17,048 --> 00:34:19,710
He didn't... he didn't believe
in credit.

564
00:34:19,784 --> 00:34:21,911
No cash withdrawals.
No ATM.

565
00:34:21,987 --> 00:34:24,421
Was that other ticket for you?

566
00:34:24,489 --> 00:34:26,548
Were you going to Athens?

567
00:34:28,560 --> 00:34:31,825
Originally, but we were
both having second thoughts.

568
00:34:31,897 --> 00:34:34,331
Well, l saw the beginning
of that show--

569
00:34:34,399 --> 00:34:36,629
his speech to the audience.

570
00:34:36,701 --> 00:34:38,896
Look, that was
just Embry being Embry.

571
00:34:38,970 --> 00:34:40,699
He was going for shock value.

572
00:34:40,772 --> 00:34:44,173
He was leaving;
l was a sophomore.

573
00:34:44,242 --> 00:34:47,302
l mean, l thought
that he would call from Europe

574
00:34:47,379 --> 00:34:50,576
and maybe l would meet up
with him in the summer.

575
00:34:50,649 --> 00:34:52,674
l never heard from him.

576
00:34:56,454 --> 00:34:59,821
You have unusually kind eyes.

577
00:35:02,594 --> 00:35:05,427
See you around, Detective.

578
00:35:09,868 --> 00:35:11,096
l'm Wade Handler.

579
00:35:11,169 --> 00:35:12,500
l'm a cop.

580
00:35:18,476 --> 00:35:21,604
You don't have to share
if you don't want to.

581
00:35:21,680 --> 00:35:24,615
l don't even know what to say.

582
00:35:24,683 --> 00:35:25,741
Uh...

583
00:35:28,353 --> 00:35:31,481
l'd find tollbooth tickets
and credit card receipts

584
00:35:31,556 --> 00:35:35,617
for bars in towns
l didn't think l'd been to.

585
00:35:35,694 --> 00:35:39,391
One day l went out to my car

586
00:35:39,464 --> 00:35:41,796
and there's a dent in the front.

587
00:35:41,866 --> 00:35:44,733
l look closer.

588
00:35:44,803 --> 00:35:49,467
There's blood
and some brown hair.

589
00:35:52,544 --> 00:35:56,742
l still don't know
what happened.

590
00:35:56,815 --> 00:35:58,783
Maybe it was a cat.

591
00:36:02,854 --> 00:36:04,253
There was an incident
two years ago

592
00:36:04,322 --> 00:36:06,517
involving an undergraduate
student and illegal drugs.

593
00:36:06,591 --> 00:36:08,786
Right. What do you want to know
about Embry Larkin?

594
00:36:08,860 --> 00:36:10,157
Well, he got himself arrested.

595
00:36:10,228 --> 00:36:11,718
l want to know
what he was selling.

596
00:36:11,796 --> 00:36:12,888
Was it heroin?

597
00:36:12,998 --> 00:36:14,989
Heroin? Embry?

598
00:36:15,066 --> 00:36:15,998
Are you kidding?

599
00:36:16,067 --> 00:36:17,898
l'm not kidding.

600
00:36:17,969 --> 00:36:19,664
No, no, he wasn't
into that shit.

601
00:36:19,738 --> 00:36:21,899
They put him on Ritalin
when he was three

602
00:36:21,973 --> 00:36:24,339
you know, your standard
A.D.D. misdiagnosis.

603
00:36:25,910 --> 00:36:28,071
Okay, um...

604
00:36:30,849 --> 00:36:32,749
Basically, he was
taking Wellbutrin

605
00:36:32,817 --> 00:36:35,786
which is sort of like having
a perfect cup of coffee.

606
00:36:35,854 --> 00:36:39,255
You know, it was great for work,
great for repetitive tasks.

607
00:36:39,324 --> 00:36:40,586
Add in some Paxil

608
00:36:40,658 --> 00:36:42,785
which is anti-depression,
anti-anxiety--

609
00:36:42,861 --> 00:36:45,193
you know, that general sense
of well-being.

610
00:36:45,263 --> 00:36:46,355
Was he selling it?

611
00:36:46,431 --> 00:36:49,628
Look, Embry's dad was rich
and Embry's mom was rich

612
00:36:49,701 --> 00:36:52,101
and they died
when he was three or four

613
00:36:52,170 --> 00:36:54,195
making him doubly rich,
so... no.

614
00:36:54,272 --> 00:36:55,933
So, what'd it do?

615
00:36:56,041 --> 00:36:59,408
Made him normal,
you know, when he took it.

616
00:38:25,964 --> 00:38:29,229
La-la-la

617
00:38:29,300 --> 00:38:34,397
La-la-la, la-la-la...

618
00:38:34,472 --> 00:38:36,064
Katie...

619
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:38,952
l heard my name whispered...

620
00:40:39,097 --> 00:40:44,262
''Katie. Katie.''

621
00:40:44,335 --> 00:40:47,930
There was somebody on the
other side of the row of books.

622
00:40:48,006 --> 00:40:49,906
l think it was my old boyfriend.

623
00:40:49,974 --> 00:40:50,963
l think he's back.

624
00:40:51,075 --> 00:40:53,407
l'm almost certain l saw him
in his car.

625
00:40:53,478 --> 00:40:55,275
l think he's been watching me.

626
00:40:55,346 --> 00:40:57,143
And how does that make you feel?

627
00:40:57,215 --> 00:40:58,477
Nervous...

628
00:40:58,549 --> 00:41:01,916
elated...

629
00:41:02,020 --> 00:41:03,317
scared.

630
00:41:03,388 --> 00:41:06,755
l want to see him, but...

631
00:41:06,824 --> 00:41:11,284
but scared
that l want to see him.

632
00:41:11,362 --> 00:41:12,693
Why do you say scared?

633
00:41:12,764 --> 00:41:15,255
Because l lost a part
of myself with him.

634
00:41:15,333 --> 00:41:17,460
l just dissolved.

635
00:41:21,005 --> 00:41:22,802
He was like a drug.

636
00:41:22,874 --> 00:41:27,277
And he was locked
inside the library with you?

637
00:41:27,345 --> 00:41:28,869
l think so, yes.

638
00:41:28,946 --> 00:41:31,039
But you hadn't seen him
in two years?

639
00:41:31,115 --> 00:41:32,639
l know how this sounds.

640
00:41:32,717 --> 00:41:35,345
Katie, you fell asleep
in an old library

641
00:41:35,420 --> 00:41:38,878
which is terrifying under
the best of circumstances.

642
00:41:38,956 --> 00:41:42,949
You're facing your graduation,
the completion of your thesis

643
00:41:43,094 --> 00:41:46,188
job interviews...
life-changing transitions.

644
00:41:46,264 --> 00:41:48,198
You need to make allowances

645
00:41:48,266 --> 00:41:51,201
for the emotions
that this will bring up.

646
00:41:51,269 --> 00:41:52,702
Yeah?

647
00:41:52,770 --> 00:41:56,706
He convinced her
she could be an artist.

648
00:41:56,774 --> 00:41:59,971
They were going to live
in a houseboat in Amsterdam...

649
00:42:00,044 --> 00:42:02,205
a sailboat off the coast
of Sardinia.

650
00:42:02,280 --> 00:42:05,511
He'd compose, she'd sing
and tell him he was a genius.

651
00:42:05,583 --> 00:42:08,552
Please, l'll have a double order
of escape fantasy

652
00:42:08,619 --> 00:42:10,246
and a side of running away.

653
00:42:10,321 --> 00:42:11,913
He was losing interest?

654
00:42:12,056 --> 00:42:13,216
l saw it coming.

655
00:42:13,291 --> 00:42:15,555
He'd replaced her in his show.

656
00:42:15,626 --> 00:42:17,093
That bastard hurt her.

657
00:42:17,161 --> 00:42:20,324
You know, she hasn't
dated anyone in two years.

658
00:42:20,398 --> 00:42:22,059
Was he a jealous guy?

659
00:42:22,133 --> 00:42:26,832
He didn't like her friends,
particularly the guy friends--

660
00:42:26,904 --> 00:42:30,499
particularly, one friend--
this guy, Harrison Hobart.

661
00:42:30,575 --> 00:42:32,509
He felt threatened by me.

662
00:42:32,577 --> 00:42:36,206
Katie and l are close,
and one day he was being

663
00:42:36,280 --> 00:42:40,273
a bit of a bully psychologically
and l said something.

664
00:42:40,351 --> 00:42:41,613
He turned on me.

665
00:42:41,686 --> 00:42:44,314
He just started poking me
in the chest

666
00:42:44,389 --> 00:42:46,289
with his... with his finger

667
00:42:46,357 --> 00:42:48,917
until, finally,
l stopped backing up.

668
00:42:48,993 --> 00:42:52,895
You know, l didn't realize
he had a bottle in his hand.

669
00:42:52,964 --> 00:42:54,898
He put you in the hospital.

670
00:42:54,966 --> 00:42:58,265
Yeah, well,
it was only overnight.

671
00:42:58,336 --> 00:43:01,237
Why didn't you press charges?

672
00:43:01,305 --> 00:43:03,899
lf you had pressed charges

673
00:43:03,975 --> 00:43:06,705
Katie might've held it
against you?

674
00:43:06,778 --> 00:43:12,148
Yeah, probably.

675
00:43:12,216 --> 00:43:14,707
You see

676
00:43:14,786 --> 00:43:16,913
Embry didn't want to admit it

677
00:43:17,054 --> 00:43:19,215
but Katie and l had
much more in common

678
00:43:19,290 --> 00:43:20,814
than the two of them did...

679
00:43:20,892 --> 00:43:22,917
and he apologized, so...

680
00:43:23,060 --> 00:43:26,393
What is your relationship
with Katie?

681
00:43:26,464 --> 00:43:28,432
Oh, man, l wish l knew.

682
00:43:28,499 --> 00:43:29,830
You dating her?

683
00:43:32,703 --> 00:43:33,692
l don't know.

684
00:43:33,771 --> 00:43:34,897
Well, sort of.

685
00:43:34,972 --> 00:43:38,669
Well, either you are
or you're not... right?

686
00:43:38,743 --> 00:43:43,874
ls this about Embry
or is this about Katie?

687
00:43:54,859 --> 00:43:58,955
l remember my dad leaving.

688
00:43:59,063 --> 00:44:02,590
Almost my first memory.

689
00:44:02,667 --> 00:44:06,000
He said, ''l love you.

690
00:44:06,070 --> 00:44:08,470
You can't come with me.''

691
00:44:08,539 --> 00:44:13,977
My mom turned the heat down
to 55 to save money.

692
00:44:15,680 --> 00:44:20,447
l just remember this...

693
00:44:20,518 --> 00:44:25,478
feeling of... emptiness...

694
00:44:28,793 --> 00:44:32,092
...always being cold.

695
00:45:17,742 --> 00:45:19,369
Sam...

696
00:46:21,439 --> 00:46:25,102
-Hey.
-Hey.

697
00:46:32,583 --> 00:46:34,574
l hope l'm not
interrupting anything.

698
00:46:34,652 --> 00:46:35,584
Oh, well...

699
00:46:35,653 --> 00:46:38,383
big night.

700
00:46:46,130 --> 00:46:47,461
l saw Embry.

701
00:46:47,531 --> 00:46:50,364
l think he's back
and l think he's watching me.

702
00:46:50,434 --> 00:46:52,265
Where did you see him?

703
00:46:52,336 --> 00:46:54,327
l saw him outside of class.

704
00:46:54,405 --> 00:46:56,430
l saw him get into his car.

705
00:46:56,507 --> 00:46:58,600
You want to...
you want to sit down?

706
00:46:58,676 --> 00:47:00,644
You're kind of making me
nervous.

707
00:47:05,883 --> 00:47:06,872
Are you afraid of him?

708
00:47:07,018 --> 00:47:08,280
ls that why you're here?

709
00:47:10,321 --> 00:47:12,380
l'm just afraid.

710
00:47:12,456 --> 00:47:16,256
Okay.

711
00:47:16,327 --> 00:47:17,885
l'll look into it.

712
00:47:20,498 --> 00:47:22,489
Thanks.

713
00:47:22,566 --> 00:47:25,433
You know, l'm not
really doing anything.

714
00:47:25,503 --> 00:47:28,336
You're welcome
to hang out if you want.

715
00:47:34,545 --> 00:47:35,807
Okay.

716
00:47:35,880 --> 00:47:37,848
Okay.

717
00:47:52,329 --> 00:47:54,923
So... why did you become a cop?

718
00:47:54,999 --> 00:47:56,830
Oh, l don't know.

719
00:47:56,901 --> 00:47:59,927
l, um... l had some issues.

720
00:48:00,004 --> 00:48:01,835
l was screwing up.

721
00:48:01,906 --> 00:48:06,343
My uncle had a badge
and he cut me a break.

722
00:48:06,410 --> 00:48:09,072
What kind of issues?

723
00:48:09,146 --> 00:48:12,172
Extreme...

724
00:48:12,249 --> 00:48:15,878
extreme substance abuse.

725
00:48:15,953 --> 00:48:17,614
Being a cop help?

726
00:48:17,688 --> 00:48:19,883
Oh, no.

727
00:48:19,957 --> 00:48:21,447
Uh-uh.

728
00:48:21,525 --> 00:48:22,685
What do you mean?

729
00:48:22,760 --> 00:48:27,129
Well, l got a pocketful
of Get-Out-Of-Jail-Free cards

730
00:48:27,198 --> 00:48:29,632
and l never changed anything.

731
00:48:29,700 --> 00:48:32,168
Then l used up all the cards.

732
00:48:37,108 --> 00:48:40,100
Setting the foundation.

733
00:48:43,447 --> 00:48:46,177
Recreational logging.

734
00:48:48,986 --> 00:48:51,284
Squirrel.

735
00:48:53,023 --> 00:48:54,581
Who took all these?

736
00:48:54,658 --> 00:48:57,218
Self-timer.

737
00:48:57,294 --> 00:48:58,761
Ex-fiancee.

738
00:48:58,829 --> 00:49:03,391
She got tired
of The Handler Show.

739
00:49:03,467 --> 00:49:05,867
Yeah, when things
start going too good

740
00:49:05,936 --> 00:49:08,598
l can't help myself,
l got to mess 'em up.

741
00:49:08,672 --> 00:49:11,232
lt's my M.O., anyway.

742
00:49:13,511 --> 00:49:15,274
Finished product.

743
00:49:22,386 --> 00:49:24,286
Excuse me.

744
00:50:13,671 --> 00:50:17,539
Can you take me home now,
please?

745
00:50:20,010 --> 00:50:21,773
Katie?

746
00:50:21,846 --> 00:50:23,473
You scared me.

747
00:50:27,184 --> 00:50:29,948
Harrison, l'm...
l completely forgot.

748
00:50:30,087 --> 00:50:31,952
l'm sorry.

749
00:50:32,089 --> 00:50:32,953
You lied.

750
00:50:33,090 --> 00:50:33,954
You lied to me.

751
00:50:34,091 --> 00:50:35,615
l'm a... l'm a total idiot.

752
00:50:35,693 --> 00:50:38,127
l'm just... l'm completely
deluding myself!

753
00:50:38,195 --> 00:50:40,493
No, you're not an idiot!

754
00:50:40,564 --> 00:50:42,429
You're not an idiot.

755
00:50:44,668 --> 00:50:47,569
Katie,
l got to tell you something

756
00:50:47,638 --> 00:50:51,165
and l should've told you
a long time ago.

757
00:50:51,242 --> 00:50:54,973
l think...

758
00:50:55,112 --> 00:50:57,808
you're kind...

759
00:50:57,882 --> 00:51:01,249
beautiful... and talented

760
00:51:01,318 --> 00:51:04,685
and l... l love you.

761
00:51:04,755 --> 00:51:06,620
What?

762
00:51:09,393 --> 00:51:12,590
Uh... l'm in love with you.

763
00:51:12,663 --> 00:51:15,393
l think l've always
been in love with you.

764
00:51:15,466 --> 00:51:17,093
Harrison...

765
00:51:17,167 --> 00:51:20,466
But, you know,
you don't have to say anything.

766
00:51:22,840 --> 00:51:26,367
You're great...

767
00:51:26,443 --> 00:51:30,812
and... you're kind and organized

768
00:51:30,881 --> 00:51:33,315
and one of the smartest
people l know

769
00:51:33,384 --> 00:51:36,376
and anyone would be so lucky
to be with you.

770
00:51:39,723 --> 00:51:44,717
Harrison... Harrison...

771
00:54:10,941 --> 00:54:14,433
l go away for a while
and look what happens.

772
00:54:14,511 --> 00:54:18,140
You let the whole place
fall apart.

773
00:54:19,983 --> 00:54:21,575
The police are looking for you.

774
00:54:21,652 --> 00:54:24,450
l don't really want to talk
to the police right now.

775
00:54:24,521 --> 00:54:26,751
You've been messing
with me for two weeks.

776
00:54:26,824 --> 00:54:28,621
More like three.

777
00:54:28,692 --> 00:54:30,182
You're proud of yourself?

778
00:54:30,260 --> 00:54:31,591
You think this is fun?

779
00:54:31,662 --> 00:54:33,425
Katie, look...

780
00:54:33,497 --> 00:54:37,763
This... this isn't
going to work.

781
00:54:41,538 --> 00:54:43,631
What happened to you?

782
00:54:43,707 --> 00:54:45,197
Where have you been?

783
00:54:45,275 --> 00:54:46,572
l went traveling--

784
00:54:46,643 --> 00:54:49,942
lndia... Asia.

785
00:54:50,013 --> 00:54:52,345
l lived and worked.

786
00:54:52,416 --> 00:54:54,816
l made my own money.

787
00:54:54,885 --> 00:54:58,184
l had to see
what was out there

788
00:54:58,255 --> 00:55:00,815
to know the value
of what is here...

789
00:55:00,891 --> 00:55:03,689
the value of this.

790
00:55:22,913 --> 00:55:26,872
Do you know
what my big goal has been?

791
00:55:26,950 --> 00:55:29,475
lt's been to stop thinking...

792
00:55:29,553 --> 00:55:30,679
to not think

793
00:55:30,754 --> 00:55:33,587
to not think that every time
the phone rang it was you!

794
00:55:33,657 --> 00:55:35,522
To not think that
every piece of mail

795
00:55:35,592 --> 00:55:36,923
in my mailbox was from you!

796
00:55:37,060 --> 00:55:38,618
To not think

797
00:55:38,695 --> 00:55:41,061
that every person
l'd see approaching was you.

798
00:55:41,131 --> 00:55:43,031
l thought about you
every bit as much

799
00:55:43,100 --> 00:55:44,362
as you thought about me.

800
00:55:44,434 --> 00:55:46,925
l don't believe you.

801
00:55:47,070 --> 00:55:50,972
Katie l was afraid
to say this before.

802
00:55:55,979 --> 00:55:58,311
l love you.

803
00:56:28,645 --> 00:56:30,442
Katie.

804
00:56:31,815 --> 00:56:34,079
Hi, Katie Burke.

805
00:56:34,151 --> 00:56:35,482
Do you know anything

806
00:56:35,552 --> 00:56:37,918
about somebody being
in the tunnel?

807
00:56:37,988 --> 00:56:41,924
Because the door was open
and it's not supposed to be open

808
00:56:42,025 --> 00:56:44,585
and it's to remain closed
at all times

809
00:56:44,661 --> 00:56:46,390
unless you're maintenance

810
00:56:46,463 --> 00:56:49,364
and you haven't been around
to ask about it

811
00:56:49,433 --> 00:56:51,094
and l'm supposed to ask.

812
00:56:51,168 --> 00:56:55,298
No, l don't. l'm busy.

813
00:56:55,372 --> 00:56:57,101
That's not very nice.

814
00:56:59,610 --> 00:57:02,579
Should l tell you what l know?

815
00:57:02,646 --> 00:57:06,377
l was going to, but now maybe
l've changed my mind.

816
00:57:06,450 --> 00:57:09,442
What are you talking about?

817
00:57:10,921 --> 00:57:15,654
Harrison Hobart is missing.

818
00:57:17,894 --> 00:57:19,987
That's two, isn't it?

819
00:57:22,599 --> 00:57:24,794
Embry is definitely back.

820
00:57:24,868 --> 00:57:26,358
l know l should've told you
right away

821
00:57:26,436 --> 00:57:27,596
but l'm overdue on my thesis

822
00:57:27,671 --> 00:57:30,606
which is essentially one long
string of endless numbers

823
00:57:30,674 --> 00:57:31,902
and finals are coming up

824
00:57:32,042 --> 00:57:33,566
and Embry has always had

825
00:57:33,644 --> 00:57:36,670
a sort of... chemical aversion
to Harry Hobart

826
00:57:36,747 --> 00:57:39,545
and l don't... l don't know
if he would do anything.

827
00:57:39,616 --> 00:57:42,642
l mean, he might, but this...
this whole experience is

828
00:57:42,719 --> 00:57:44,914
so far out of my normal range
of things.

829
00:57:45,055 --> 00:57:46,147
Okay, slow down.

830
00:57:46,223 --> 00:57:48,020
Are you saying that Embry

831
00:57:48,091 --> 00:57:50,787
might have done something
to Harrison?

832
00:57:50,861 --> 00:57:54,194
l don't know.

833
00:57:54,264 --> 00:57:55,595
l'm not sure.

834
00:57:55,666 --> 00:57:58,931
l don't know why l feel
so comfortable with you.

835
00:57:59,002 --> 00:58:00,663
l know that l shouldn't.

836
00:58:00,737 --> 00:58:02,568
God, what am l doing here?

837
00:58:08,178 --> 00:58:10,009
lt's okay.

838
00:58:10,080 --> 00:58:11,775
No, it's not.

839
00:58:17,854 --> 00:58:22,052
Get down on it,
get down on it

840
00:58:22,125 --> 00:58:24,559
Get down on it,
get down on it...

841
00:58:24,628 --> 00:58:27,028
lf somebody told me
this was the rest of my life

842
00:58:27,097 --> 00:58:28,758
l think l'd kill myself
right now.

843
00:58:28,832 --> 00:58:30,459
This isn't the rest
of your life.

844
00:58:30,534 --> 00:58:31,466
This is right now.

845
00:58:31,535 --> 00:58:32,524
Yeah, well, right now

846
00:58:32,602 --> 00:58:34,160
my friends are
out somewhere else

847
00:58:34,237 --> 00:58:35,829
and they're having a great time.

848
00:58:35,906 --> 00:58:37,840
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

849
00:58:37,908 --> 00:58:38,840
Your old friends.

850
00:58:38,909 --> 00:58:41,844
Yeah.

851
00:58:41,912 --> 00:58:43,402
l'm just blowing off steam.

852
00:58:43,480 --> 00:58:44,674
l'm sorry, all right?

853
00:58:44,748 --> 00:58:48,377
So what's up
with the Larkin kid, huh?

854
00:58:48,452 --> 00:58:51,012
Apparently he had
a car waiting-- a CTS Limo.

855
00:58:51,088 --> 00:58:53,556
lt was supposed to take him
to the airport.

856
00:58:53,623 --> 00:58:54,555
He never got in.

857
00:58:54,624 --> 00:58:56,421
Never used the airline tickets.

858
00:58:56,493 --> 00:58:58,393
The girlfriend says he's back.

859
00:58:58,462 --> 00:59:02,091
What's this girl like, Wade?

860
00:59:02,165 --> 00:59:04,395
What do you mean?

861
00:59:04,468 --> 00:59:06,993
ls she a nice girl?

862
00:59:07,070 --> 00:59:08,002
Yeah.

863
00:59:08,071 --> 00:59:09,299
Smart?

864
00:59:09,373 --> 00:59:11,204
What do you think? Yeah.

865
00:59:11,274 --> 00:59:13,765
What about you, Wade?

866
00:59:13,844 --> 00:59:15,573
Are you smart?

867
00:59:18,281 --> 00:59:20,545
Harrison is
a responsible young man

868
00:59:20,617 --> 00:59:23,245
and we know he holds you
in high regard.

869
00:59:23,320 --> 00:59:25,083
He thinks of you
as a confidante.

870
00:59:25,155 --> 00:59:26,383
This is so unlike him.

871
00:59:26,456 --> 00:59:29,084
We're obviously very worried.

872
00:59:29,159 --> 00:59:32,925
lf there's anything at all
you could tell us...

873
00:59:34,464 --> 00:59:37,900
l don't know where Harrison is.

874
00:59:37,968 --> 00:59:39,560
l'm as worried as you are.

875
00:59:39,636 --> 00:59:41,604
This is difficult for me to ask

876
00:59:41,671 --> 00:59:44,435
and in no way
am l impugning you.

877
00:59:44,508 --> 00:59:47,102
Was Harrison using drugs?

878
00:59:53,650 --> 00:59:55,413
What?

879
00:59:55,485 --> 00:59:58,215
He missed his father's birthday.

880
00:59:58,288 --> 01:00:01,917
Can you think of anyone
he might have gone to visit...

881
01:00:01,992 --> 01:00:07,020
any new friends...
people we don't know about?

882
01:00:07,097 --> 01:00:10,464
Uh, Harrison doesn't even
drink coffee.

883
01:00:10,534 --> 01:00:12,934
He worries about damaging
the instrument.

884
01:00:13,003 --> 01:00:14,698
We're grasping for anything.

885
01:00:17,007 --> 01:00:21,103
l'm sure that there is...
some explanation.

886
01:00:24,681 --> 01:00:27,115
What do you think you're doing?

887
01:00:27,184 --> 01:00:28,276
Finding you.

888
01:00:28,351 --> 01:00:31,149
Do you know where Harrison is?

889
01:00:31,221 --> 01:00:33,485
The tree-hugger?

890
01:00:33,557 --> 01:00:34,956
l don't really keep tabs on him.

891
01:00:35,025 --> 01:00:36,151
Have you seen him lately?

892
01:00:36,226 --> 01:00:38,194
Wouldn't you like to know.

893
01:00:38,261 --> 01:00:41,424
You piss me off
like nobody else, you know that?

894
01:00:41,498 --> 01:00:42,430
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

895
01:00:42,499 --> 01:00:44,160
What you going to do about it?

896
01:00:44,234 --> 01:00:48,796
l want you to come away with me
to the country house.

897
01:00:48,872 --> 01:00:50,430
Where is Harrison?

898
01:00:50,507 --> 01:00:53,601
l'll tell you
at the country house.

899
01:00:57,681 --> 01:01:01,048
Sure he was in love with her.

900
01:01:01,117 --> 01:01:02,744
Harrison's a good guy.

901
01:01:02,819 --> 01:01:05,447
He mooned around,
but he was sweet.

902
01:01:05,522 --> 01:01:08,184
He got his name
on scientific papers

903
01:01:08,258 --> 01:01:09,850
when he was about 12.

904
01:01:09,926 --> 01:01:12,622
So, what did he know
about anything?

905
01:01:12,696 --> 01:01:15,426
Do you think it was odd
that he still liked a girl

906
01:01:15,499 --> 01:01:18,696
who hadn't shown him any real
interest in over two years?

907
01:01:20,337 --> 01:01:23,568
l thought it was
the opposite of odd.

908
01:01:23,640 --> 01:01:29,840
Guys are drawn to her
like bugs around a bug lamp.

909
01:01:29,913 --> 01:01:33,212
For four years, l've had
the privilege of watching it.

910
01:01:33,283 --> 01:01:34,910
That bother you, Julie?

911
01:01:36,853 --> 01:01:41,586
Think you see the horns
of jealousy?

912
01:01:41,658 --> 01:01:43,956
You got my angle?

913
01:01:44,027 --> 01:01:47,758
You might want to ask yourself
why you're so interested in her.

914
01:01:47,831 --> 01:01:52,097
They think it's
a coltish vulnerability

915
01:01:52,168 --> 01:01:54,762
but it's just self-obsession.

916
01:01:54,838 --> 01:01:58,205
The pea brain says,
''She needs saving''

917
01:01:58,275 --> 01:02:01,836
and the pea brain says,
''l can save her''

918
01:02:01,912 --> 01:02:04,676
and then she doesn't
notice them.

919
01:02:04,748 --> 01:02:08,149
So, they go crazy.

920
01:02:08,218 --> 01:02:12,780
lt's about the missing dad
and... validation.

921
01:02:15,158 --> 01:02:17,126
She just needs a friend.

922
01:03:27,964 --> 01:03:29,727
Embry.

923
01:03:44,080 --> 01:03:45,138
Embry!

924
01:03:45,215 --> 01:03:49,049
Detective.

925
01:03:49,119 --> 01:03:51,519
What are you doing here?

926
01:03:51,588 --> 01:03:53,783
Oh, right.

927
01:03:53,857 --> 01:03:56,052
Stalking Katie, l remember.

928
01:03:56,126 --> 01:04:00,324
Listen, l'm...
l'm looking for her.

929
01:04:00,397 --> 01:04:02,592
l think this kid,
Embry Larkin, is back.

930
01:04:02,666 --> 01:04:03,724
Who told you that?

931
01:04:03,800 --> 01:04:05,893
She told you that Embry's back?

932
01:04:06,002 --> 01:04:07,026
She's seen him?

933
01:04:07,103 --> 01:04:09,697
Do you think she's
with him right now?

934
01:04:09,773 --> 01:04:11,900
l know. l'll keep
asking you questions

935
01:04:11,975 --> 01:04:13,806
and you keep
not answering them.

936
01:04:13,877 --> 01:04:16,573
Look, l'm just concerned
about her.

937
01:04:22,686 --> 01:04:25,314
Detective, you seem like
a pretty good guy--

938
01:04:25,388 --> 01:04:27,754
you do, you do--

939
01:04:27,824 --> 01:04:31,851
but Embry was the
love of her life.

940
01:04:31,928 --> 01:04:34,590
Ouch!

941
01:04:34,664 --> 01:04:38,065
He who snatched the maidenhead
from the maiden.

942
01:04:38,134 --> 01:04:39,761
l shouldn't have said that.

943
01:04:39,836 --> 01:04:41,929
Do you want to come upstairs
and have a drink?

944
01:04:45,241 --> 01:04:49,200
Bad Samantha! Bad Sam!

945
01:04:49,279 --> 01:04:51,372
l better go now.

946
01:05:47,103 --> 01:05:49,765
You fell asleep.

947
01:05:49,839 --> 01:05:53,002
lt's been a long time
since l've watched you sleep.

948
01:07:19,395 --> 01:07:21,795
Where were we?

949
01:07:32,609 --> 01:07:33,598
Oh, no.

950
01:07:33,676 --> 01:07:38,511
-What did you do to Harrison?
-What did you do to Harrison?

951
01:07:44,654 --> 01:07:46,417
What did you do to him?

952
01:07:52,695 --> 01:07:54,356
Evisceration.

953
01:07:54,430 --> 01:07:55,590
Vivisection.

954
01:07:55,665 --> 01:07:56,927
Drawn and quartered.

955
01:07:58,167 --> 01:08:00,328
The quartering act.
Dismemberment.

956
01:08:00,403 --> 01:08:02,803
And set him on fire.

957
01:08:02,872 --> 01:08:06,000
You arrogant, preening... bore!

958
01:08:11,514 --> 01:08:14,881
Who are you running back to,
Katie?

959
01:08:14,951 --> 01:08:16,282
Not the tree-hugger.

960
01:08:16,352 --> 01:08:17,614
Not the townie cop.

961
01:08:17,687 --> 01:08:20,315
You're already
the young professional--

962
01:08:20,390 --> 01:08:24,156
passionless, desiccated....

963
01:08:24,227 --> 01:08:25,694
smug.

964
01:08:40,243 --> 01:08:43,440
He slipped that under my door
a couple of nights ago.

965
01:08:43,513 --> 01:08:45,481
Where's the old place?

966
01:08:53,957 --> 01:08:55,219
Suite 408.

967
01:08:57,760 --> 01:08:58,692
l'm sorry.

968
01:08:58,761 --> 01:09:01,594
l should have told you sooner.

969
01:09:01,664 --> 01:09:03,256
Can l keep this?

970
01:09:05,635 --> 01:09:06,863
And l saw him again.

971
01:09:07,003 --> 01:09:11,235
l went to his country house.

972
01:09:11,307 --> 01:09:14,606
l told him l never wanted
to see him again.

973
01:09:14,677 --> 01:09:16,736
Well, l want to see him.

974
01:09:16,813 --> 01:09:18,838
l need to see this guy.

975
01:09:22,251 --> 01:09:26,585
Detective, please do me a favor.

976
01:09:26,656 --> 01:09:28,647
Sure.

977
01:10:04,961 --> 01:10:08,055
l'm done.

978
01:10:08,131 --> 01:10:09,826
Everyone's done.

979
01:10:09,899 --> 01:10:11,298
l'm not done.

980
01:10:11,367 --> 01:10:12,925
Detective!

981
01:10:13,002 --> 01:10:16,938
You should arrest that man.

982
01:10:17,040 --> 01:10:18,405
lt's medicinal-- glaucoma.

983
01:10:18,474 --> 01:10:19,736
l've got a prescription.

984
01:10:19,809 --> 01:10:22,107
Just don't play
any Grateful Dead

985
01:10:22,178 --> 01:10:23,839
or you're all going in.

986
01:10:23,913 --> 01:10:25,881
Okay, we'll try not to.

987
01:12:12,355 --> 01:12:14,585
Hey, Jed, what do you say?

988
01:12:14,657 --> 01:12:16,056
Hey, long time, no see, Handler.

989
01:12:16,125 --> 01:12:18,855
Listen, if you're not too busy
dipping into the drug seizures

990
01:12:18,928 --> 01:12:20,691
you want to take a look at these
for me?

991
01:12:20,763 --> 01:12:24,062
Do a little compare and contrast
of the handwriting.

992
01:12:24,133 --> 01:12:25,395
''My summer vacation.

993
01:12:25,468 --> 01:12:27,936
Working for the
Supreme Court Justice.''

994
01:12:28,004 --> 01:12:28,936
l bet he got in.

995
01:12:29,071 --> 01:12:29,935
Thanks, Jed.

996
01:12:30,072 --> 01:12:32,267
Hey, Handler, are you happy?

997
01:12:32,341 --> 01:12:33,968
You seem happy.

998
01:12:35,211 --> 01:12:36,803
Last Chance Dance?

999
01:12:36,879 --> 01:12:39,279
Yeah, that's where they
call the wonks

1000
01:12:39,348 --> 01:12:42,249
out of their cubbyholes
and try to mate them.

1001
01:12:42,318 --> 01:12:43,910
That would be you.

1002
01:12:43,986 --> 01:12:46,045
Wonks?
l'm a scientist. Pure science.

1003
01:12:46,122 --> 01:12:47,089
lt's sexy.

1004
01:12:47,156 --> 01:12:48,384
Very sexy.

1005
01:12:48,457 --> 01:12:50,186
Yeah, you want to go?

1006
01:12:50,259 --> 01:12:52,955
Did she just ask me out?

1007
01:12:53,095 --> 01:12:54,585
l believe so.

1008
01:12:54,664 --> 01:12:55,596
l'll go.

1009
01:12:55,665 --> 01:12:57,565
Katie! Oh, my God.

1010
01:12:57,633 --> 01:12:58,930
Look what came!

1011
01:12:59,001 --> 01:13:00,628
You got the job!

1012
01:13:00,703 --> 01:13:03,729
l didn't look at this at all.

1013
01:13:03,806 --> 01:13:06,104
There's a card in it.

1014
01:13:06,175 --> 01:13:07,472
$10,000?

1015
01:13:07,543 --> 01:13:10,910
For what,
shipping all of your antiques?

1016
01:13:11,013 --> 01:13:12,446
Airline tickets?

1017
01:13:18,187 --> 01:13:20,553
Bob?

1018
01:13:25,328 --> 01:13:26,761
Oh, come on.

1019
01:13:26,829 --> 01:13:29,491
Don't be one of those
annoying people who wins

1020
01:13:29,565 --> 01:13:31,829
then acts like winning
doesn't matter.

1021
01:13:37,873 --> 01:13:39,067
Are you okay?

1022
01:13:39,141 --> 01:13:41,075
Yeah.

1023
01:13:41,143 --> 01:13:44,738
You know, you could've told me
that Embry was back.

1024
01:13:44,814 --> 01:13:47,078
l know.

1025
01:13:49,185 --> 01:13:53,713
You're thinking about the cop,
aren't you?

1026
01:13:53,789 --> 01:13:55,120
Maybe.

1027
01:13:55,191 --> 01:13:58,456
Okay, visualize this with me.

1028
01:13:58,527 --> 01:14:00,085
You're down in New York

1029
01:14:00,162 --> 01:14:03,290
consulting with Lou Gerstner
or the head of GE

1030
01:14:03,366 --> 01:14:06,665
telling them how to buy
South American countries

1031
01:14:06,736 --> 01:14:09,296
but on the weekends
you fly back up here

1032
01:14:09,372 --> 01:14:11,897
to hang out with the cop,
do cop things

1033
01:14:11,974 --> 01:14:13,464
maybe go to cop mixers.

1034
01:14:13,542 --> 01:14:16,136
l like the cop.

1035
01:14:16,212 --> 01:14:19,181
Yeah, um, l can see that.

1036
01:14:24,987 --> 01:14:28,354
How much money
do detectives make?

1037
01:14:28,424 --> 01:14:32,190
Didn't your mother tell you
that's a rude question to ask?

1038
01:14:32,261 --> 01:14:34,695
No. She was always
asking people that.

1039
01:14:34,764 --> 01:14:37,824
lf l guess right,
do l get a prize?

1040
01:14:37,900 --> 01:14:38,958
Maybe.

1041
01:14:41,237 --> 01:14:43,933
A million bucks.

1042
01:14:44,040 --> 01:14:45,940
l didn't want to insult you.

1043
01:14:46,042 --> 01:14:48,169
You're not going to insult me.

1044
01:14:48,244 --> 01:14:51,338
Look, you don't do police work
for the money.

1045
01:14:51,414 --> 01:14:52,938
What do you do it for?

1046
01:14:53,015 --> 01:14:54,414
l don't know really.

1047
01:14:54,483 --> 01:14:57,611
Most people do it because
that's what their fathers' did.

1048
01:14:57,687 --> 01:14:59,211
ls that what your father did?

1049
01:14:59,288 --> 01:15:01,722
He was a teacher.

1050
01:16:08,758 --> 01:16:12,524
Hey. Hey...

1051
01:16:12,595 --> 01:16:15,189
Oh... l guess l was dreaming.

1052
01:16:15,264 --> 01:16:17,892
l was... just having a dream.

1053
01:16:24,340 --> 01:16:27,639
What are you thinking about?

1054
01:16:27,710 --> 01:16:29,075
That l just woke up

1055
01:16:29,145 --> 01:16:31,909
next to a girl
that l don't really know

1056
01:16:32,047 --> 01:16:33,639
and l'm not hungover.

1057
01:16:37,153 --> 01:16:39,087
How does that feel?

1058
01:16:42,391 --> 01:16:47,158
Like free-falling through space.

1059
01:16:59,308 --> 01:17:02,141
Can l tell you something
and you won't get mad?

1060
01:17:05,948 --> 01:17:09,145
You don't seem like a cop to me.

1061
01:17:09,218 --> 01:17:11,880
You don't seem
that happy doing it.

1062
01:17:11,954 --> 01:17:15,856
Can l tell you something?

1063
01:17:15,925 --> 01:17:18,826
l'm thinking about quitting.

1064
01:17:18,894 --> 01:17:20,885
What would you do?

1065
01:17:20,996 --> 01:17:26,332
l'd probably go up to my cabin
and hammer some nails

1066
01:17:26,402 --> 01:17:28,529
figure out the meaning of life.

1067
01:17:28,604 --> 01:17:31,198
Okay, l'll come.

1068
01:17:31,273 --> 01:17:34,037
l didn't ask you yet.

1069
01:17:34,109 --> 01:17:36,202
Sure, you did.

1070
01:17:36,312 --> 01:17:40,442
l feel like an anvil has been
removed from my ankle.

1071
01:17:40,516 --> 01:17:42,484
Finishing your thesis?

1072
01:17:42,551 --> 01:17:46,112
Finishing my thesis,
school, everything.

1073
01:17:46,188 --> 01:17:48,679
That's a good thing.

1074
01:17:48,757 --> 01:17:54,559
You know, um... l know you're
moving down to New York

1075
01:17:54,630 --> 01:17:59,693
after graduation, and...

1076
01:17:59,768 --> 01:18:03,329
the transition
from school can be tough.

1077
01:18:03,405 --> 01:18:08,035
So l want you to know
you can always call me, okay?

1078
01:18:09,912 --> 01:18:11,971
'Cause l'm down there a lot,
and...

1079
01:18:12,047 --> 01:18:15,847
l mean, l was actually wondering
if maybe, um...

1080
01:18:17,887 --> 01:18:20,355
...if l could call you.

1081
01:18:25,961 --> 01:18:31,558
l was nervous about telling you
that l'm feeling better

1082
01:18:31,634 --> 01:18:35,570
and that l won't be needing
to see you anymore.

1083
01:18:37,273 --> 01:18:39,741
Thank you for making it easier.

1084
01:18:48,150 --> 01:18:49,640
Hey, Handler.

1085
01:18:49,718 --> 01:18:51,310
Hey, Jed.

1086
01:18:53,022 --> 01:18:55,149
You really off the job?

1087
01:18:55,224 --> 01:18:56,248
l really am.

1088
01:18:56,325 --> 01:18:58,486
You probably don't care
but the samples were a match.

1089
01:18:58,561 --> 01:19:01,029
The same person wrote the flyer
and the college application.

1090
01:19:01,096 --> 01:19:02,256
Well, that's just aces, Jed.

1091
01:19:02,331 --> 01:19:03,389
You keep up the good work.

1092
01:19:03,465 --> 01:19:05,433
See you around.

1093
01:19:07,570 --> 01:19:10,869
Only thing is... ink tests show

1094
